# Middleware Layer
#
# Contains Express middleware functions:
#   authMiddleware.js    — protect() : validates JWT, attaches req.user
#                        — restrictTo(...roles) : role-based access control
#   errorMiddleware.js   — Global (err, req, res, next) error handler
#   uploadMiddleware.js  — Multer configuration for medical report uploads
#   validate.js          — Runs express-validator result, propagates ApiError on failure
#
# Rule: Middleware functions receive (req, res, next) and:
#   - Either transform req (auth) or intercept and respond (validation, errors)
#   - Call next() to pass to the next handler, or next(err) to skip to error handler
#   - Never contain business logic
#
# Populated in: Milestone 15 (Middleware — Auth & Authorization)
#               Milestone 11 (Input Validation)
#               Milestone 9  (Centralized Error Handling)
